<paragraph blockId="5.[136,1452,410,1085]" pageId="5" pageNumber="206">
The protologue of 
<taxonomicName box="[345,507,410,436]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Hieracium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="5" pageNumber="206" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="elisaeanum">
<emphasis box="[345,507,410,436]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="206">H. elisaeanum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
includes a complete description in Latin, followed by the provenance and a mention of two gatherings: “In 
<collectingRegion box="[384,472,446,472]" country="Spain" name="Aragon" pageId="5" pageNumber="206">Aragon</collectingRegion>
. australi (Sierra de Javalambre ad rup. calcar. alt. 
<quantity box="[1021,1107,446,473]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="206" unit="m" value="2000.0">2000 m</quantity>
, Reverchon, 
<date box="[1252,1354,446,472]" pageId="5" pageNumber="206" value="1891-07">Jul. 1891</date>
et 1892) et regno Valent. (Sierra de Castalla in rupestrib. calc., alt. 
<quantity box="[770,926,482,509]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.6" metricValueMax="1.8" metricValueMin="1.4" pageId="5" pageNumber="206" unit="m" value="1600.0" valueMax="1800.0" valueMin="1400.0">1400–1800 m</quantity>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="G. Rigo" authorityName="G. Rigo" box="[937,996,483,509]" class="Insecta" family="Rhyparochromidae" genus="Porta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="212" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Porta</taxonomicName>
et Rigo, 
<date box="[1095,1202,482,508]" pageId="5" pageNumber="206" value="1890-07">Jul. 1890</date>
)”. The protologue also includes this information: “1879 
<superScript attach="none" box="[500,516,518,532]" fontSize="6" pageId="5" pageNumber="206">ter</superScript>
. 
<taxonomicName authority="Arv. Touv." authorityName="Arv. Touv." authorityYear="2021" box="[531,911,518,545]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Hieracium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="5" pageNumber="206" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="elisaeanum" status="sp. n.">Hieracium Elisaeanum Arv. Touv.</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[918,978,519,545]" pageId="5" pageNumber="206" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
in sched. pl. exs. Reverch. Decemb. 1892 et in litt. ad Hervier (
<taxonomicName box="[371,508,554,580]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Hieracium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="5" pageNumber="206" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="baeticum">H. baeticum</taxonomicName>
et flocciferum Arv. 
<collectionCode box="[733,751,555,581]" name="Tavera, Department of Geology and Geophysics" pageId="5" pageNumber="206">T</collectionCode>
. prius in plant. exs. Reverch. anni 1891, 
<taxonomicName authority="Porta et Rigo" authorityName="Porta et Rigo" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Hieracium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="5" pageNumber="206" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="bellidifolium">H. bellidifolium Porta et Rigo</taxonomicName>
ap. 
<taxonomicName authority=", Vegt." authorityName="Vegt." box="[265,397,591,617]" class="Insecta" family="Rhyparochromidae" genus="Porta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="206" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Porta, Vegt.</taxonomicName>
p. 44! non Scheele)”.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[136,1452,410,1085]" pageId="5" pageNumber="206">
We have found a specimen, herbarium sheet with barcode 
<collectionCode box="[824,839,626,652]" country="France" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15763" name="Museum National d' Histoire Naturelle, Paris (MNHN) - Vascular Plants" pageId="5" pageNumber="206" type="Herbarium">P</collectionCode>
03686242, that belong to the 
<taxonomicName box="[1157,1216,627,653]" class="Insecta" family="Rhyparochromidae" genus="Porta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="206" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Porta</taxonomicName>
&amp; Rigo’s exsiccatum mentioned in the protologue (regno Valent., Sierra de Castalla in rupestrib. calc., alt. 
<quantity box="[1083,1239,662,689]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.6" metricValueMax="1.8" metricValueMin="1.4" pageId="5" pageNumber="206" unit="m" value="1600.0" valueMax="1800.0" valueMin="1400.0">1400–1800 m</quantity>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="G. Rigo" authorityName="G. Rigo" box="[1251,1310,663,689]" class="Insecta" family="Rhyparochromidae" genus="Porta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="212" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Porta</taxonomicName>
et Rigo, 
<date pageId="5" pageNumber="206" value="1890-07">Jul. 1890</date>
). This sheet bears four complete and well-developed plants, and an original printed label, annotated as: “Nº. / 
<taxonomicName authority="Scheele Prodr. II." authorityName="Scheele Prodr. II." box="[136,622,734,761]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Hieracium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="5" pageNumber="206" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="bellidifolium">Hieracium bellidifolium Scheele Prodr. II.</taxonomicName>
261. / Valentina, in rupestribus Sierra Castalla / sol. calcar. 
<quantity metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.6" metricValueMax="1.8" metricValueMin="1.4" pageId="5" pageNumber="206" unit="m" value="1600.0" valueMax="1800.0" valueMin="1400.0">1400–1800 m</quantity>
.s.m. Jul. / 
<taxonomicName authority="G. Rigo" authorityName="G. Rigo" box="[281,340,771,797]" class="Insecta" family="Rhyparochromidae" genus="Porta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="212" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Porta</taxonomicName>
et Rigo. iter II Hispanicum 1890” (
<figureCitation box="[742,811,770,796]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[136,229,2028,2050]" captionTargetBox="[196,1391,190,2004]" captionTargetId="figure-24@6.[196,1391,190,2004]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3. Lectotype of Hieracium elisaeanum Arv.-Touv. ex Willk. in P (barcode P03686242) and capitula details of the specimen.— Image by courtesy of the Muséum National d’Histoire Naturelle (Herbarium P), reproduced with permission" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5413225" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5413225/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="206">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
). This specimen is therefore a 
<typeStatus box="[1157,1244,771,797]" pageId="5" pageNumber="206">syntype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName box="[1282,1445,770,796]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Hieracium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="5" pageNumber="206" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="elisaeanum">
<emphasis box="[1282,1445,770,796]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="206">H. elisaeanum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and according to Art. 9.12 of the 
<emphasis box="[505,552,807,833]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="206">
<collectionCode box="[505,552,807,833]" country="Colombia" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/xsgz-nxkh" name="Instituto de Ciencias Naturales, Museo de Historia Natural" pageId="5" pageNumber="206">ICN</collectionCode>
</emphasis>
, it has precedence in the 
<typeStatus box="[834,937,806,832]" pageId="5" pageNumber="206">lectotype</typeStatus>
designation before the uncited specimens and the cited and not quoted illustrations that comprise the remaining original material, if such really exist.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[136,1452,410,1085]" pageId="5" pageNumber="206">
Fortunately, this 
<typeStatus box="[377,464,879,905]" pageId="5" pageNumber="206">syntype</typeStatus>
at 
<collectionCode box="[498,513,879,905]" country="France" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15763" name="Museum National d' Histoire Naturelle, Paris (MNHN) - Vascular Plants" pageId="5" pageNumber="206" type="Herbarium">P</collectionCode>
is well preserved and complete, and shows several of the diagnostic characters used to differentiate this taxon as the apex of the rhizome with dense, long hairs, cauline leaves elliptical to ovate–lanceolate; capitula (1–)2–3; involucre 7–9(–11) mm long, with numerous stellate and few glandular hairs; achenes (1.5–) 
<quantity metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.55" metricValueMax="2.8" metricValueMin="2.3" pageId="5" pageNumber="206" unit="mm" value="2.55" valueMax="2.8" valueMin="2.3">2.3–2.8 mm</quantity>
long, and matches the traditional concept and current use of the name (see Arvet–Touvet 1913, 
<bibRefCitation author="Zahn, K. H." box="[1246,1369,986,1012]" pageId="5" pageNumber="206" pagination="1 - 492" refId="ref9642" refString="Zahn, K. H. (1930) Hieracium. In: Ascherson, P. &amp; Graebner, P. (Eds.) Synopsis der mitteleuropaischen Flora 12 (1). Gebruder Borntraeger, Leipzig, pp. 1 - 492." type="book chapter" year="1930">Zahn 1930</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Sell, P. D. &amp; West, C." pageId="5" pageNumber="206" pagination="358 - 410" refId="ref9011" refString="Sell, P. D. &amp; West, C. (1976) Hieracium L. In: Tutin, T. G., Heywood, V. H., Burges, N. A., Moore, D. M., Valentine, D. H., Walters, S. M. &amp; Webb, D. A. (Eds.) Flora Europaea, vol. 4. Cambridge University Press, Cambridge, pp. 358 - 410." type="book chapter" year="1976">Sell &amp; West 1976</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Mateo, G. &amp; Egido, F." box="[270,513,1022,1049]" pageId="5" pageNumber="206" refId="ref8422" refString="Mateo, G. &amp; Egido, F. del (2017) Estudio monografico de los generos Hieracium y Pilosella en Espana. Con referencias a Portugal y los Pirineos franceses. Monografias de Botanica Iberica, nº 20, Jolube, Jaca, 422 pp." type="book" year="2017">Mateo &amp; Egido 2017</bibRefCitation>
, Mateo 
<emphasis box="[604,654,1022,1048]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="206">et al</emphasis>
. 2017). Accordingly, we designate as the 
<typeStatus box="[1127,1230,1022,1048]" pageId="5" pageNumber="206">lectotype</typeStatus>
of 
<emphasis box="[1269,1296,1023,1048]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="206">
<collectionCode box="[1269,1293,1023,1048]" country="Finland" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15618" name="University of Helsinki" pageId="5" pageNumber="206" type="Herbarium">H</collectionCode>
.
</emphasis>
the specimen kept at 
<collectionCode box="[218,234,1059,1085]" country="France" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15763" name="Museum National d' Histoire Naturelle, Paris (MNHN) - Vascular Plants" pageId="5" pageNumber="206" type="Herbarium">P</collectionCode>
.
</paragraph>
